 American Revolution, reminding us that not all Loyalists were members of the elite and that their motivations were a complicated medley of political beliefs, religious convictions, and self-interest.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aAmerican loyalistszMiddle Atlantic States. 4aAmerican Studies : American Studies. 4aHistory : American History. 4aReligion and Spirituality : American Religion. 7aHISTORY / United States / Revolutionary Period (1775-1800).2bisacsh1 aBodle, Wayne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCrothers, A. Glenn, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFingerhut, Eugene R., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFingerhut, Eugene R., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aFowler, David J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGroth, Michael E., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMacGregor, Doug, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTiedemann, Joseph S., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTiedemann, Joseph S., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aVenables, Robert W., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aVenables, Robert W., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013z978311148737340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143842598640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438425986423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438425986/original  a978-3-11-148737-3  SUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles